name: PhysicalTherapyEvaluationSNOMED
title: Physical Therapy Evaluation (SNOMED)
description: This set of values contains SNOMED-CT codes for physical therapy evaluation procedures including both evaluation and re-evaluation procedures.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains physical therapy evaluation and re-evaluation procedures.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who receive physical therapy evaluations (including both initial evaluation and re-evaluation procedures)),(Inclusion Criteria: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who receive physical therapy evaluations, including those defined generically as physical therapy assessment procedures and specifically as physical therapy diagnostic assessment procedures. . This element may map to the "Assessment" or "Encounter" Category of the Quality Data Model,),(Exclusion Criteria: Intervention procedures.)
